LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 322
BY WAYS AND MEANS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO SALARIES OF JUDGES; AMENDING SECTION 59-502, IDAHO CODE, TO
3 REVISE A PROVISION REGARDING THE SALARY OF THE JUSTICES OF THE SUPREME
4 COURT; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 59-502, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 59-502. SALARIES OF JUDGES. (1) Commencing on July 1, 2024 2025, the
9 salary of the justices of the supreme court shall be one hundred sixty-nine
10 thousand five hundred eight dollars ($169,508) one hundred eighty-six thou-
11 sand five hundred eight dollars ($186,508) per annum.
12 (2) Commencing on July 1, 2023, judges of the court of appeals shall re-
13 ceive an annual salary in an amount of eight thousand dollars ($8,000) less
14 than the annual salary of a supreme court justice.
15 (3) Commencing on July 1, 2017, district judges shall receive an an-
16 nual salary in an amount of six thousand dollars ($6,000) less than the an-
17 nual salary of a judge of the court of appeals.
18 (4) Commencing on July 1, 2023, magistrate judges shall receive an an-
19 nual salary in an amount of eight thousand dollars ($8,000) less than the an-
20 nual salary of a district judge.
21 (5) Salaries shall be paid on regular pay periods not less frequently
22 than monthly as determined by order of the supreme court as due out of the
23 state treasury, but no justice of the supreme court or judge of the district
24 court or magistrate shall be paid his salary, or any part thereof, unless
25 he shall first take and subscribe an oath that there is not in his hands any
26 matter in controversy not decided by him that has been finally submitted for
27 his consideration and determination thirty (30) days prior to his taking and
28 subscribing said oath.
29 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
30 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
31 July 1, 2025.

